Module iu.util.type
Package edu.iu.type

Class IuTypeKey

java.lang.Object
edu.iu.type.IuTypeKey
public class IuTypeKey extends Object
Hash key for use with generic types.

Java controls instances of Class, but instance control for other implementations of the Type interface is not clearly defined. The JDK typically, but is not required to, produces a new instance each time a generic type is referred to. This class inspects the generic type to determine strict equality as:

  • Same instances are equal. Recursive base case: all leaf nodes are Class; and Class is strictly a leaf node.
  • Both instanceof matching exactly one of:
    • ParameterizedType
      • Recursively checks raw type and all type arguments
    • TypeVariable
      • Checks variable name
      • Recursively checks bounds
    • WildcardType
      • Recursively check upper and lower bounds
    • GenericArrayType
      • Recursively check component type
